title: Wolf Pack freshman baseball player dies overnight
text: Share Updated: 12:20 pm RENO, Nev. -- The University of Nevada, Reno athletics department has reported the death of 19-year-old Austin Gorrell, a freshman catcher for the Nevada baseball team.An official statement from the University states that Gorrell died overnight. He had a known previous medical condition. He enrolled at Nevada this fall after graduating from John W. North High School in Riverside, California in the spring. Grief counselors are available for Nevada students and staff. Information on services will be announced as it becomes available.
